go_data.justification: SUP-12 specifically binds to UGUGUG stretch in intron 1A of the unc-60 gene.
SUP-12 cooperatively regulates muscle-specific alternative splicing of the unc-60 gene with ASD-2.
SUP-12 is expressed in body wall muscles and regulates muscle-specific splicing of the unc-60 gene.
As an RNA-binding protein, SUP-12 is expected to be localized to the nucleus to regulate pre-mRNA processing.
